  "texts": [
    "However, the architectural simulator approaches either focus on single systems or rely on simplified assumptions (e.g., fixed-duration timesteps), while the micro-operation cost estimates fail to capture system-level performance characteristics of parallel workload execution across neurocores.Optimization efforts have explored partitioning and mapping strategies for neuromorphic platforms [3], [23], [26], [27], [42], [49], [55], [57], [61], though most work remains limited to simulators without validation on real systems.",
